        public static void setDefaultFactory(DrawFactory factory)
        Set a custom draw factory for the current thread. This is a fallback, for operations where usercode can't set a graphics context. Preferably use the rendering hint Drawable.DRAW_FACTORY to set the factory.(${t_759a53c035f44991857cccc44cb5e6b2})
        Parameters:
        factory - the custom factory or null to reset/remove the default factory(${t_559946e5eeed4ef99afd633e2c09f7e2})
